						"copy": "<div style= \"text-align:left; font-size: 26px; font-weight: bold; line-height:125%\" >Does your SaaS security architecture protect against phishing, data loss, and shadow IT?\n </div><br>\n<div style= \"text-align:left; font-size: 16px; color:rgb(0, 86, 220);font-weight: normal; line-height:125%\" >\nProtect your inbox and data with a Zero Trust approach\n </div><br>\n\n![A1 LP Banner - SaaS](//cf-assets.www.cloudflare.com/slt3lc6tev37/1Uql8sbRG07ZiGCSatGWct/8e2ebb4c2fa966a3e4746073152e6fb6/a1-gated-lp-banner.png)\n\nWith the shift to the cloud and remote work, more organizations are turning to cloud email solutions within Microsoft 365 and Google Workspace — as much as 70% of organizations worldwide, per Gartner®.\n\nHowever, cloud email has also become one of the largest attack surfaces — attracting phishing, malware, spoofing, business email compromise (BEC), and other modern threats.\n\nA Zero Trust approach is the simple and scalable way to stay ahead of emerging threats, reduce phishing incidents, and improve efficiency.\n\n__Download this whitepaper to:__\n\n- Review traditional vs. modern SaaS security\n- Learn how to combat new phishing categories while reducing email security complexity\n- Understand how Zero Trust simplifies user access to critical applications, and keeps your organization safe from both external and internal attacks\n- See how CASB + cloud email security optimally performs when implemented within a Zero Trust architecture",
